Yes, they can work together but you must=
 feed both instances the same seed list.  It will then decide based on doma=
ins which seeds (and discovered URIs) each will crawl.

These two propertie=
s shows each crawler instance what its name (localName) is and how many cra=
wlers (crawlerCount) it is &quot;sharing&quot; the crawl with.

&lt;property name=3D&quot;loc=
alName&quot;      value=3D&quot;1&quot; /&gt;
&lt;property name=3D&quot;crawlerCount&quot;   value=3D&quot;2&quot; /=
&gt;

If one crawler finds URIs that the other crawler is suppose to crawl, it=
 places those URIs in the diversions folder.  You have to manually move tho=
se diversion files to the other crawler instance (with some modifications t=
o the file before placing them in the actions folder of the other crawler i=
nstance).

--David

